<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jardim, Jaime A." journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736" pagination="491 - 497" refId="B6422701" refString="Jardim, Jaime A., Almeida, Sergio M., Simone, Luiz L., 2017. Redescription of Acanthochitona terezae. Journal of Conchology 42 (6): 491 - 497" title="Redescription of Acanthochitona terezae" volume="42" year="2017">Jardim et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
): Mollusc with many plates on surface. Tegument with many white spots mainly on apical region. Girdle white with transverse orange bands. Intermediate valves trapezoidal to oblong in outline, subcarinate, weakly beaked (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6448414" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">9</figureCitation>
<figureCitation captionStartId="F6448419" pageId="0" pageNumber="62736">a</figureCitation>
). Pustules on latero-pleural area round to oval, randomly arranged; each pustule convex, bearing 4-7 pores on superior to median surface. Tail valve with prominent, submedian mucro; postmucronal area concave. Dorsal side of girdle covered with minute elongated spicules; spicule height about 8-9 times as long as wide, sculptured by longitudinal parallel fissures. Sutural tufts with elongated spicules and sculptured by longitudinal fissures.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
